{"article_id":"GGC85xQOXX2116O6","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Story highlights","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"Secretary of state completes more than five hours of sometimes contentious hearings","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"Libya wanted to provide security ,","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"but lacked the capacity ,","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"Clinton said","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"Clinton 's appearance before Congress was delayed due to health issues","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"At times angry and choked with emotion ,","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"Secretary of State Hillary Clinton on Wednesday took on Republican critics of her department 's handling of the September terrorist attack in Libya","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"that killed the U.S. ambassador and three other Americans ,","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"but repeatedly distanced herself from a direct role in specific situations .","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"`` As I have said many times since September 11 ,","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"I take responsibility , ''","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"Clinton told two long-anticipated congressional hearings","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"examining the attack","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"that became a major issue in the November presidential election .","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"Conservative Republicans challenged Clinton on the lack of security at the diplomatic compound in Benghazi ,","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"where Ambassador Christopher Stevens and three others were killed ,","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"as well as the erroneous account","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"provided four days later by U.N . Ambassador Susan Rice","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"that the attack grew spontaneously from a protest over an anti-Islam film","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"produced in the United States .","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"Sen. Ron Johnson , a tea party backed Wisconsin Republican","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"serving his first term ,","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"persistently questioned Clinton on Wednesday morning about what he described as Rice `` purposely misleading '' the American people .","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"`` We were misled","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"that there were supposedly protests","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"and something sprang out of that ,","depth":12},{"id":27,"text":"an assault sprang out of that","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"and that was easily ascertained that that was not the fact , ''","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"Johnson said ,","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"adding","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"that `` the American people could have known that within days . ''","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"Clinton , senators clash over Benghazi","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"MUST WATCH Clinton , senators clash over Benghazi","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"04:11","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"JUST WATCHED Chaffetz :","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"Clinton faces hard questions","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"MUST WATCH Chaffetz :","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"Clinton faces hard questions","depth":12},{"id":42,"text":"03:36","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"Clinton testimony emotional , fiery","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":13},{"id":47,"text":"Clinton testimony emotional , fiery","depth":13},{"id":48,"text":"02:47","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":12},{"id":50,"text":"Townsend :","depth":13},{"id":51,"text":"Benghazi hearing waste of time","depth":13},{"id":52,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":13},{"id":53,"text":"MUST WATCH Townsend :","depth":14},{"id":54,"text":"Benghazi hearing waste of time","depth":14},{"id":55,"text":"03:31","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"Shouting","depth":14},{"id":57,"text":"and gesturing with her arms in frustration ,","depth":14},{"id":58,"text":"Clinton shot back :","depth":13},{"id":59,"text":"`` With all due respect , the fact is we had four dead Americans .","depth":13},{"id":60,"text":"Was it because of a protest","depth":14},{"id":61,"text":"or was it because of guys out for a walk one night decided","depth":15},{"id":62,"text":"they 'd go kill some Americans ? ''","depth":15},{"id":63,"text":"Her fists shaking ,","depth":13},{"id":64,"text":"she continued :","depth":13},{"id":65,"text":"`` What difference , at this point , does it make ?","depth":13},{"id":66,"text":"It is our job to figure out what happened","depth":14},{"id":67,"text":"and do everything","depth":16},{"id":68,"text":"we can","depth":16},{"id":69,"text":"to prevent it from ever happening again , senator . ''","depth":15},{"id":70,"text":"Later Johnson ,","depth":14},{"id":71,"text":"interviewed by CNN 's Erin Burnett ,","depth":14},{"id":72,"text":"said","depth":13},{"id":73,"text":"he still did not think","depth":13},{"id":74,"text":"Clinton answered his question .","depth":13},{"id":75,"text":"`` The American people also have the right","depth":16},{"id":76,"text":"to be told the truth , ''","depth":16},{"id":77,"text":"said Johnson .","depth":15},{"id":78,"text":"`` They have an expectation","depth":15},{"id":79,"text":"that this administration , this president will be honest with them .","depth":15},{"id":80,"text":"And so it makes a big deal of difference .","depth":13},{"id":81,"text":"I 'll tell you what ,","depth":13},{"id":82,"text":"I was surprised by Secretary Clinton 's reaction to that . ''","depth":13},{"id":83,"text":"Another conservative , Sen. Rand Paul of Kentucky , told Clinton","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"she should have been fired","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"for not reading cables from Stevens and others in Libya .","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"Later in the day , conservative GOP Rep. Jeff Duncan of South Carolina accused Clinton of `` national security malpractice ''","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"by letting the Benghazi consulate `` become a death trap . ''","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"Duncan also questioned Clinton 's claim","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"of taking responsibility ,","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"noting","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"she still had her job","depth":12},{"id":92,"text":"and the State Department officials","depth":14},{"id":93,"text":"cited for culpability by an independent review","depth":14},{"id":94,"text":"also remained on the payroll , though on forced leave","depth":14},{"id":95,"text":"pending possible further steps .","depth":14},{"id":96,"text":"At both hearings ,","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"which together totaled more than five hours ,","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"Clinton acknowledged the `` systemic breakdown ''","depth":14},{"id":99,"text":"cited by an Accountability Review Board","depth":15},{"id":100,"text":"she appointed","depth":15},{"id":101,"text":"and noted","depth":14},{"id":102,"text":"she had accepted all 29 of its recommendations ,","depth":14},{"id":103,"text":"adding","depth":13},{"id":104,"text":"her department was taking additional steps","depth":14},{"id":105,"text":"to increase security at U.S. diplomatic facilities around the world .","depth":14},{"id":106,"text":"However , she also told both the Senate Foreign Relations Committee and House Foreign Affairs Committee","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"that she had no direct role in the handling of requests by Stevens and other diplomats for increased security","depth":13},{"id":108,"text":"that were denied ,","depth":13},{"id":109,"text":"saying :","depth":13},{"id":110,"text":"`` I did n't see those requests .","depth":14},{"id":111,"text":"They did n't come to me . ''","depth":14},{"id":112,"text":"In reference to the erroneous talking points by Rice","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"that were aired on September 16 ,","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"Clinton told the Senate panel","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"that she was focused at that time on ensuring the safety of U.S. personnel at other facilities","depth":13},{"id":116,"text":"where protests were taking place .","depth":13},{"id":117,"text":"`` I was pretty occupied about keeping our people safe ,","depth":13},{"id":118,"text":"doing what needed to be done , ''","depth":13},{"id":119,"text":"Clinton said ,","depth":12},{"id":120,"text":"adding","depth":12},{"id":121,"text":"`` I was n't involved in the talking points process . ''","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"At one point , Clinton attempted to wrap up the issue ,","depth":10},{"id":123,"text":"saying :","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"`` If you wish to fault the administration ,","depth":13},{"id":125,"text":"it 's that we did n't have a clear picture ,","depth":13},{"id":126,"text":"and we probably did n't do as clear a job","depth":13},{"id":127,"text":"explaining","depth":16},{"id":128,"text":"that we did not have a clear picture ,","depth":16},{"id":129,"text":"until days later ,","depth":15},{"id":130,"text":"creating what I think","depth":15},{"id":131,"text":"are legitimate questions . ''","depth":15},{"id":132,"text":"The independent report from the review board said","depth":11},{"id":133,"text":"it did not find `` that any individual U.S. government employee engaged in misconduct or willfully ignored his or her responsibilities ''","depth":12},{"id":134,"text":"leading up to the attack .","depth":12},{"id":135,"text":"However , one State Department official resigned","depth":12},{"id":136,"text":"and three others were placed on administrative leave","depth":12},{"id":137,"text":"after the report was released in December .","depth":11},{"id":138,"text":"One of the GOP 's harshest critics of the administration over the Benghazi attack , Sen. John McCain of Arizona , called Clinton 's testimony unsatisfactory .","depth":9},{"id":139,"text":"He said","depth":11},{"id":140,"text":"her department had yet to fully disclose all e-mails and other communication from Stevens and others in Benghazi ,","depth":11},{"id":141,"text":"noting","depth":11},{"id":142,"text":"the American people ,","depth":13},{"id":143,"text":"including the family and loved ones of those killed ,","depth":13},{"id":144,"text":"deserved full answers .","depth":12},{"id":145,"text":"Critics also complain","depth":10},{"id":146,"text":"the assailants remain at large ,","depth":10},{"id":147,"text":"and Clinton noted","depth":11},{"id":148,"text":"that `` we continue to hunt the terrorists","depth":13},{"id":149,"text":"responsible for the attacks in Benghazi","depth":13},{"id":150,"text":"and are determined to bring them to justice . ''","depth":12},{"id":151,"text":"She told Wednesday 's hearings","depth":11},{"id":152,"text":"that the FBI is pursuing what she called `` very positive leads . ''","depth":11},{"id":153,"text":"In her opening statement to both panels , Clinton said","depth":10},{"id":154,"text":"the Benghazi attack did n't happen in a vacuum","depth":11},{"id":155,"text":"but was part of a `` broader strategic challenge in North Africa and the wider region . ''","depth":11},{"id":156,"text":"She defended her department 's response ,","depth":10},{"id":157,"text":"saying","depth":13},{"id":158,"text":"there was `` timely '' and `` exceptional '' coordination between the State Department and the Pentagon on the night of the attack","depth":13},{"id":159,"text":"`` No delays in decision making .","depth":14},{"id":160,"text":"No denials of support from Washington or from the military , ''","depth":14},{"id":161,"text":"Clinton said .","depth":13},{"id":162,"text":"The review panel 's report `` said","depth":14},{"id":163,"text":"our response saved American lives in real time","depth":14},{"id":164,"text":"-- and it did , ''","depth":13},{"id":165,"text":"she added .","depth":12},{"id":166,"text":"Clinton also said","depth":10},{"id":167,"text":"she directed the response to the attack from the State Department that night","depth":11},{"id":168,"text":"and `` stayed in close contact with officials from across our government and the Libyan government . ''","depth":11},{"id":169,"text":"In addition , Clinton said","depth":10},{"id":170,"text":"she immediately took steps","depth":11},{"id":171,"text":"to beef up security at U.S. posts around the world","depth":12},{"id":172,"text":"and to implement the review panel 's 29 recommendations .","depth":12},{"id":173,"text":"Clinton made clear","depth":11},{"id":174,"text":"that the security situation in North Africa and the Middle East remained threatening in the wake of the Arab Spring upheaval ,","depth":12},{"id":175,"text":"with longtime leaders ousted in Egypt , Tunisia and Libya .","depth":12},{"id":176,"text":"The fledgling Libyan leadership turned out to be unable to fulfill traditional security commitments to the U.S. diplomatic compound ,","depth":12},{"id":177,"text":"she said .","depth":12},{"id":178,"text":"`` What I found with the Libyans was willingness","depth":13},{"id":179,"text":"but not capacity , ''","depth":13},{"id":180,"text":"she said .","depth":12},{"id":181,"text":"Clinton also warned","depth":11},{"id":182,"text":"that weapons from Libya have turned up in Algeria and elsewhere ,","depth":12},{"id":183,"text":"adding","depth":13},{"id":184,"text":"that `` this Pandora 's Box","depth":15},{"id":185,"text":"if you will ''","depth":15},{"id":186,"text":"represented a major security threat .","depth":14},{"id":187,"text":"`` The Arab Spring has ushered in a time","depth":13},{"id":188,"text":"when al Qaeda is on the rise , ''","depth":13},{"id":189,"text":"she said .","depth":12},{"id":190,"text":"`` The world in many ways is even more dangerous","depth":12},{"id":191,"text":"because we lack a central command","depth":14},{"id":192,"text":"[ in al Qaeda ]","depth":14},{"id":193,"text":"and have instead these nodes","depth":14},{"id":194,"text":"that are scattered throughout North Africa and other places . ''","depth":14},{"id":195,"text":"Clinton expressed particular concern at events in Mali ,","depth":11},{"id":196,"text":"where well-armed Tuareg militia ,","depth":14},{"id":197,"text":"who had been working for former Libyan leader Moammar Gadhafi ,","depth":14},{"id":198,"text":"came home","depth":13},{"id":199,"text":"just as al Qaeda in the Islamic Maghreb","depth":14},{"id":200,"text":"( AQIM )","depth":14},{"id":201,"text":"gravitated toward the area .","depth":13},{"id":202,"text":"The size and topography of northern Mali , with its endless desert and caves , made for a long but necessary struggle ,","depth":12},{"id":203,"text":"she said ,","depth":12},{"id":204,"text":"adding","depth":12},{"id":205,"text":"that `` we can not permit northern Mali to become a safe haven . ''","depth":12},{"id":206,"text":"Overall ,","depth":11},{"id":207,"text":"she said ,","depth":11},{"id":208,"text":"at least 20 U.S. diplomatic outposts `` are under a serious threat environment","depth":11},{"id":209,"text":"as I speak to you . ''","depth":11},{"id":210,"text":"Wednesday 's committee appearances were some of the last acts for Clinton","depth":7},{"id":211,"text":"before she leaves her post","depth":8},{"id":212,"text":"as long planned ,","depth":8},{"id":213,"text":"and Clinton showed a personal side","depth":8},{"id":214,"text":"in discussing what happened .","depth":8},{"id":215,"text":"`` For me , this is not just a matter of policy , ''","depth":10},{"id":216,"text":"she told the Senate panel .","depth":10},{"id":217,"text":"`` It 's personal . ''","depth":9},{"id":218,"text":"In reference to the return of remains of the four slain Americans , Clinton said in a voice","depth":10},{"id":219,"text":"choked with emotion :","depth":10},{"id":220,"text":"`` I stood next to President Obama","depth":11},{"id":221,"text":"as the Marines carried those flag-draped caskets off the plane at Andrews .","depth":11},{"id":222,"text":"I put my arms around the mothers and fathers , sisters and brothers , sons and daughters . ''","depth":10},{"id":223,"text":"Democrats on both panels made a point","depth":8},{"id":224,"text":"of praising Clinton 's service","depth":8},{"id":225,"text":"and noted","depth":8},{"id":226,"text":"that House Republicans have voted to cut funding for diplomatic security .","depth":8},{"id":227,"text":"However , Republicans rejected any connection between budget resources and vulnerability at the Benghazi compound ,","depth":7},{"id":228,"text":"citing a report by a State Department financial officer .","depth":7},{"id":229,"text":"The hearings provided Republicans with a final opportunity","depth":8},{"id":230,"text":"to question Clinton ,","depth":10},{"id":231,"text":"considered a possible presidential contender in 2016 ,","depth":10},{"id":232,"text":"on camera","depth":9},{"id":233,"text":"before she leaves office .","depth":7},{"id":234,"text":"After the September attack , conservative Republicans focused on the issue","depth":7},{"id":235,"text":"to attack the Obama administration 's handling of the Libyan revolution and the overall Arab Spring upheaval .","depth":7},{"id":236,"text":"Several legislators made references on Wednesday to Clinton 's possible political future ,","depth":6},{"id":237,"text":"with Republican Steve Chabot of Ohio drawing a laugh from the secretary","depth":7},{"id":238,"text":"when he said :","depth":8},{"id":239,"text":"`` I wish you the best in your future endeavors .","depth":9},{"id":240,"text":"Mostly . ''","depth":9},{"id":241,"text":"Polls show strong public support for Clinton and her performance as secretary of state ,","depth":4},{"id":242,"text":"with an ABC News/Washington Post survey released Wednesday","depth":5},{"id":243,"text":"showing 67 % of respondents had a favorable impression of her .","depth":5}],"relations":[{"parent":487,"left":0,"right":486,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":486,"left":452,"right":485,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":452,"left":248,"right":451,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":248,"left":1,"ri